                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la" otherLangs="de"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2ra" to="4rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Index</title>
                                <note>Alphabetical index to Conrad of Saxony's sermons keyed to the medieval foliation.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locusGrp>
                                    <locus from="4va" to="11vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="133ra" to="133vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                </locusGrp>
                                <title type="desc">Sermons </title>
                                <rubric>Sermo de maria magdalena</rubric>
                                <incipit>Vade in pace et cetera lucas <del>x</del> vii (Luke 7:50) hodie celebramus festum peccatorum</incipit>
                                <explicit>vii pertinentes ad diuinitatem et vii ad humanitatem et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4va" to="4va" scheme="folios"/>: Mary Magdalene (Luke 7:50);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5vb" to="5vb" scheme="folios"/>: St James (Mat. 20:22);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="7rb" to="7rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Peter (John 21:20);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="8ra" to="8ra" scheme="folios"/>: sermon on Ps. 18:13;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10vb" to="10vb" scheme="folios"/>: sermon on Mat. 22.</p>
                                    <p> After the last line on <locus from="11vb" to="11vb" scheme="folios"/> the words <quote>quere retro tali signo</quote> and a sign (there is also a reference to the folio in question by a later hand) points the reader to the continuation of the text on <locus from="133ra" to="133ra" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="12ra" to="133ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102713">Conrad of Saxony</persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Sermons on the saints</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt sermones fratris chunradi de saxonia de sanctis andree apostoli</rubric>
                                <incipit>Extendam palmas meas ad dominum Exodus ix (Exo 9:29) hoc uerbum Moysi beatus andreas apostolus potuit dicere </incipit>
                                <explicit>glorie digni sunt qui bene presunt vobis ergo bene preesse concedat qui cum patre in uni et cetera Amen</explicit>
                                <note>Agrees to a large part with the <ref target="https://books.google.se/books?id=qoJCAAAAcAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;redir_esc=y#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false">Paris 1521</ref> print (Pseudo-)Bonaventure, Sermones de sanctis de quibus et eorum, although not always in the same order. Begins with St Andrew and ends with <quote>Sermo ad prelatos</quote> (corresponds to <quote>De Rectoribus Ser. II Fo. CLXXIX</quote> in the printed version).</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="134r" to="136v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Sermons on St Andrew and St Nicholas</title>
                                <incipit>Venite post me faciam uos fieri piscatores et cetera mattheus 4 (Matt. 4:19) Consuetudo est in exercitibus quod</incipit>
                                <explicit>habebat beatus nicolaus istam consuetudinem</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="134r" to="134r" scheme="folios"/> St Andrew (Mat. 4:19;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="135r" to="135r" scheme="folios"/> St Nicholas (Ps. 32:5).</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="137r" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Sermons</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">
                                    <supplied reason="damage">deco</supplied>rem domus tue et cetera (Ps. 25:8) Decor et gloria domus consistunt in tribus </incipit>
                                <explicit>hoc est ut deo regnare placeat in nobis</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="137r" to="137r" scheme="folios"/>: sermon on Ps. 25:8;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="137v" to="137v" scheme="folios"/>: sermon on Ave maria;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="138v" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>: sermon on Pater noster.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="139ra" to="139rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="de"/>
                                <title type="desc">Sermon in German on the feast of St Nicholas</title>
                                <incipit>Ecce vere israelita in quo dolus non est (John 1:47) hevt begen wir der hochzit des rechten nothhelfers s Nycolaus</incipit>
                                <explicit>ein nothelfer is allen di sin gnade su<add place="above">o</add>echent</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="139v" to="139v" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="2" to="139" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="125" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="138" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <foliation>
                                        <locus from="12r" to="132v" scheme="folios"/>: medieval foliation <quote>I-CXXII</quote>. </foliation>
                                    <condition>Parchment worn and damaged throughout. Holes from bookworms at the beginning and end. <locus from="1" to="4" scheme="folios"/>: hole through the leaves, perhaps caused by fire. Signs of contemporary repairs in places, e.g. <locus from="89" to="89" scheme="folios"/>. Text damaged by damp in several places, e.g <locus from="23v" to="24r" scheme="folios"/>. <locus from="137" to="137" scheme="folios"/>: upper inner corner missing with loss of 2-3 words of text.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="2" ruledLines="36">
                                        <locus from="12r" to="133r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="120" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="90" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Guidelines and ruling in ink; pricking in the margins. The manuscript also contains shorter texts with a different layout.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <p>The main text on <locus from="12ra" to="133ra" scheme="folios"/> is written by at least four different hands.</p>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locusGrp>
                                        <locus from="2ra" to="11vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="133ra" to="133vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    </locusGrp>Textualis currens. </handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="12ra" to="56va" scheme="folios"/>Textualis.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-3">
                                    <locus from="56va" to="58vb" scheme="folios"/>Textualis.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-4">
                                    <locus from="58vb" to="59va" scheme="folios"/>Textualis.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-5">
                                    <locus from="60ra" to="133ra" scheme="folios"/>Textualis.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-6">
                                    <locus from="134r" to="136v" scheme="folios"/>Textualis (perhaps a new hand on <locus from="135v" to="135v" scheme="folios"/>).</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-7">
                                    <locus from="137r" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>Cursiva antiquior (no looping on <locus from="137r" to="137r" scheme="folios"/>).</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-8">
                                    <locus from="139r" to="139r" scheme="folios"/>Textualis. </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="7v" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Margins filled with additions by the scribe or a contemporary hand.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="132v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note> Additions in the margins throughout by several different hands. The main layer consists of short one or two letter markings of theological authorities, made by the scribe or a contemporary hand. In several places text is written in a small script perpendicularly in the outer margin, e.g. <locus from="46r" to="46r" scheme="folios"/>: a chapter heading. Many of these additions have been partially lost due to trimming. There are also several other examples of different glosses or additions by other medieval hands, e.g. <locus from="57v" to="57v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="85r" to="85r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="91r" to="91r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="92v" to="92v" scheme="folios"/>; and on <locus from="22r" to="22r" scheme="folios"/> in the bottom margin, a gloss in German: <quote>er nimpt ein sel di er gelt vnd wider geb Gvet vnd er daz er rechte nu<add place="above">e</add>tze vnder zer Gotes gnad uon der er rechte leb Sorig
                                            vnd geshephte des er getrivucher pleg di himelishen chrone die imer ob im sveb</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink, rubrics in red, capitals occasionally touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="12r" to="12r" scheme="folios"/>: opening plain initial over 3 lines in blue with flourishing in red. <locus from="12v" to="131r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 2 lines alternating in red and blue. <locus from="134r" to="134r" scheme="folios"/>: dentelle initial over 4 lines in gold on a blue background, frame and counterspace in red. <locus from="135r" to="135r" scheme="folios"/>: foliate initial over 4 lines in blue on a gold background, frame in red.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
                    </msPart>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
